data.description: Here is your opportunity to own a unique mid-century ranch inspired by famous architect Minoru Yamasaki, in the sought after Morningside Heights community. Truly an amazing home with a glass atrium that runs the entire depth of the home. Four-bedroom suites all with their own private baths. Floors are a combination of teak, marble and terrazzo. The kitchen with original teak cabinets and stainless steel. The living room, primary suite and foyer all with sliding glass doors that overlook the back atrium with full glass ceiling, incredible space for indoor-outdoor entertaining. The living room with 2 additional glass doors that overlook a water feature, the yard is very private with plenty of wildlife. Tremendous amount of storage space, four skylights, the home is designed for living space on one side of the home and sleeping quarters on the opposite side. Lower level with terrazzo floors large windows for great lighting and a walkout door to the side yard. The home was built in 1959 and written up in the Detroit Free Press in 1960 as the "A House that courts privacy". This is truly an amazing home, not to be missed. Highly accredited Birmingham schools. Three new furnaces in the past 2 years, water heater in 2023. A licensed Michigan realtor must accompany all showings. BATVAD
